annotationA: Spindle assembly abnormal 6 is a centriole protein that is essential for centriole assembly. It can homo-oligomerise to form a 9-fold symmetric "cartwheel" structure that plays an important part in setting the 9-fold symmetry of the assembling centriole
annotationB: Anastral spindle 2 is a centriole protein that is essential for centriole assembly, promoting the assembly of the central "cartwheel" structure. It may also have an independent role in promoting asymmetric divisions in larval neuroblasts
